"title": "4207: land, as a divine gift",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4207: land, as a divine gift",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's gift of the land of Israel is fundamental to the covenant promises made to Abraham and his descendants.</p>\n<h2>Land as part of God's creation</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:9-Gen1:10\">GEN 1:9–1:10</a></p>\n<h2>The land (Canaan) promised to Abraham</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:7\">GEN 12:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:1\">GEN 12:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:15-Gen13:17\">GEN 13:15–13:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:8\">GEN 17:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:7\">GEN 24:7</a></p>\n<h2>The boundaries of the promised land</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:18-Gen15:21\">GEN 15:18–15:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:31\">EXO 23:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num34:1-Num34:12\">NUM 34:1–34:12</a></p>\n<h2>God's promise and its gradual fulfilment</h2>\n<h3>The promise made to the patriarchs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:3-Gen26:4\">GEN 26:3–26:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:17-Gen23:20\">GEN 23:17–23:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:13\">GEN 28:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:12\">GEN 35:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:3-Gen48:4\">GEN 48:3–48:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:24-Gen50:25\">GEN 50:24–50:25</a> <em>The patriarchs maintained only a very small part of the land.  But Genesis closes with the prospect of much more.</em></p>\n<h3>The promise confirmed during the wilderness wanderings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:7-Exod3:8\">EXO 3:7–3:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:4\">EXO 6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:8\">EXO 6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:5\">EXO 13:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:11\">EXO 13:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:11-Exod32:14\">EXO 32:11–32:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:1-Exod33:3\">EXO 33:1–33:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:10-Num11:12\">NUM 11:10–11:12</a></p>\n<h3>Exploration of the promised land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:1-Num13:2\">NUM 13:1–13:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:21-Num13:25\">NUM 13:21–13:25</a></p>\n<h3>Entry delayed because of unbelief and rebellion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:27-Num13:33\">NUM 13:27–13:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:1-Num14:4\">NUM 14:1–14:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:26-Num14:35\">NUM 14:26–14:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:40-Num14:45\">NUM 14:40–14:45</a></p>\n<h3>Criticial importance of obedience in the promised land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:32-Deut5:33\">DEU 5:32–5:33</a></strong> <em>Moses, at the end of his life, urges all the Israelites always to remember the LORD and his commands; enjoyment of the land is dependent upon the people's obedience.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:10-Deut6:12\">DEU 6:10–6:12</a></p>\n<h3>Invasion of the land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:2\">JOS 1:2</a></strong> <em>The theme of the book of Joshua is the land: chapters 1–12 its invasion and conquest, chapters 13–21 its division among the Israelite tribes.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:1\">JOS 2:1</a></p>\n<h3>Gradual conquest of the land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:1\">JOS 13:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:2\">JOS 7:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:1\">JOS 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:1-Josh9:2\">JOS 9:1–9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:29-Josh10:30\">JOS 10:29–10:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:2-Josh13:6\">JOS 13:2–13:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:12\">JOS 14:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh17:12-Josh17:18\">JOS 17:12–17:18</a></p>\n<h3>The promise fulfilled</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh21:43-Josh21:45\">JOS 21:43–21:45</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Division of the land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:4-Josh23:5\">JOS 23:4–23:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Conflict with the Philistines over the land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:7-1Sam7:14\">1SA 7:7–7:14</a></strong> <em>Philistine aggression had imperilled the prospect of a full possession of the land until David overpowered them.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:21-Judg2:22\">JDG 2:21–2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:1\">JDG 13:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:11\">JDG 15:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam4:10-1Sam4:11\">1SA 4:10–4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:17-1Sam13:19\">1SA 13:17–13:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:1-1Sam17:2\">1SA 17:1–17:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:1\">1SA 31:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:7\">1SA 31:7</a></p>\n<h3>Jerusalem captured by David</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:6-2Sam5:7\">2SA 5:6–5:7</a></p>\n<h2>The land at rest and prosperous</h2>\n<h3>Under David</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:1\">2SA 7:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:1-2Sam8:6\">2SA 8:1–8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam8:14\">2SA 8:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:15-2Sam10:19\">2SA 10:15–10:19</a></p>\n<h3>Under Solomon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:4\">1KI 5:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:20-1Kgs4:21\">1KI 4:20–4:21</a></p>\n<h2>The exile and subsequent return to the land</h2>\n<h3>Losing the land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:14\">LEV 26:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:32-Lev26:33\">LEV 26:32–26:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:63-Deut28:65\">DEU 28:63–28:65</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:13\">JER 16:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:4\">JER 17:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:11\">JER 25:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer44:22\">JER 44:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:2\">LAM 5:2</a></p>\n<h3>Return to the land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:7-Jer23:8\">JER 23:7–23:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:1\">ISA 14:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:10\">ISA 35:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:5-Isa43:6\">ISA 43:5–43:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:41-Ezek20:42\">EZK 20:41–20:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:11-Ezek34:13\">EZK 34:11–34:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos9:14-Amos9:15\">AMO 9:14–9:15</a></p>",
